column1: Intrinsically very bright and/or large and/or massive galaxies
1 QSO's or any kind of active galaxy without a discernible/measured diameter are excluded
2 Constraints: d <= 2.5 GPc AND (MB < -20 OR Diam > 40 Kpc) AND must have a discernible body
3 Objets that are individually not bright and/or large enough to be included here, but are bright/large if you consider the summed contribution of close
companions are excluded, (e.g. few compact clusters listed as one entry in the ESO catalog), but intrinsically bright/large objects that are part of
multiple systems (that probably canibalized many smaller galaxies) are included
4 Caveats: Is cannot be considered complete given that there are probably many giant/luminous BGC (Brightest Galaxy in Clusters) and a few nonstellar
QSO's that are not included here
5 Sometimes objects listed here are larger and brighter than listed values due, e.g. to the presence of faint extended halos, to non-homogeinity as to
what surface brightness level those values were measured, etc
Check: 2019ApJS..243...14O - The Ogle et al. Galaxy Catalog (OGC) (Ogle+, 2019)
